histogram.Title: Channel occupancies
histogram.Description: Multiplicities of TDC signals by channel number.

histogram.Title: Good and corrupted TDC times
histogram.Description:
"Corrupted" SigCh-s (the second bin) originate from lost or corrupted data at the DAQ level. There is always a fraction of them but is should be stable over time.

Alert if the ratio of the second bin to the first one increases.

histogram.Title: TDC times per time window
histogram.Description: Number of TDC times recorded within a single 50 microsecond time window od the DAQ system.

histogram.Title: Size of identified SiPM matrix signals
histogram.Description:
SiPM matrix signals consist of 1-4 SiPM signals from the same matrix.
The plot presents frequency of recording a matrix signal with 1,2,3 and 4 SiPM signals in coincidence.

histogram.Title: Multiplicity of SiPM matrix signals in a time window
histogram.Description: Number of SiPM matrix signals identified within a single 50 microsecond time window od the DAQ system.

histogram.Title: Hit A-B time differences vs scintillator ID
histogram.Description:
Time difference between A and B sides of a hit vs ID of the scintillator recording the hit.
Should constitute a uniform band.
The edges of the band getting jagged indicate calibration going off.
Watch out for gaps indicating problematic scintillator.

histogram.Title: Multiplicity of hits in a time window
histogram.Description: Number of hits identified within a single 50 microsecond time window od the DAQ system.

histogram.Title: Multiplicity of hits per scintillator
histogram.Description: Number of hits identified in a particular scintillator.

histogram.Title: Hit TOT vs scintillator ID
histogram.Description: Time Over Threshold (calculated with the rectangular approximation) of  a hit vs ID of the scintillator recording the hit.
